1
00:00:04,788 --> 00:00:08,103
Kṛṣṇa may speak in so many
different ways about Himself,

2
00:00:08,103 --> 00:00:10,944
and they’re all accurate, 
of course,

3
00:00:11,482 --> 00:00:14,462
[Loving Embrace of Kṛṣṇa]

4
00:00:14,907 --> 00:00:21,243
but when we want to know Him,
as they say, ‘up close and personal’,

5
00:00:21,243 --> 00:00:29,618
then really that sort of vision, we’re
going to get from His devotees.

6
00:00:29,618 --> 00:00:34,496
Although He does say 
He’s everything.

7
00:00:34,496 --> 00:00:37,608
Sometimes Guru Mahārāj 
would use that

8
00:00:37,608 --> 00:00:41,996
to indicate the superiority
of Kṛṣṇa conception,

9
00:00:41,996 --> 00:00:46,232
saying, “No one makes
the same claims Kṛṣṇa does.”

10
00:00:46,232 --> 00:00:49,609
Like when He turns to Arjuna and
He goes, “Arjuna, I’m everything,

11
00:00:49,609 --> 00:00:50,951
do you know that?

12
00:00:50,951 --> 00:00:53,060
I’m everything”,

13
00:00:55,030 --> 00:00:59,142
and Arjuna’s saying, “I know that,
and I’m really sorry, in the past

14
00:00:59,142 --> 00:01:04,783
sometimes being a little too friendly
with you, since you are everything”,

15
00:01:04,783 --> 00:01:07,439
and Kṛṣṇa’s saying, 
“Well let me tell you something else,

16
00:01:07,439 --> 00:01:11,834
I actually enjoy when you forget
that I’m everything

17
00:01:11,834 --> 00:01:16,725
and just deal with Me in a friendly way.
That gives Me great happiness.”

18
00:01:16,725 --> 00:01:19,778
That’s what’s so beautiful
about Krṣṇa conception.

19
00:01:19,778 --> 00:01:22,020
Otherwise, no wonder
people don’t like God.

20
00:01:22,020 --> 00:01:27,730
They think God is this arrogant person,
owning and controlling everything,

21
00:01:27,730 --> 00:01:33,867
and just punishing people because
He’s bored or has nothing better to do.

22
00:01:33,867 --> 00:01:35,978
That’s not the Kṛṣṇa conception;

23
00:01:35,978 --> 00:01:45,180
Kṛṣṇa’s waiting to give His devotees
His loving embrace,

24
00:01:45,180 --> 00:01:49,092
as in the return of Gopa Kumār
to the spiritual world.

25
00:01:49,123 --> 00:01:55,889
Sometimes Guru Mahārāj, paraphrasing
Kṛṣṇa after He wakes up from fainting

26
00:01:55,889 --> 00:02:00,704
—He’s so happy He fainted
upon the arrival of Gopa Kumār—

27
00:02:00,704 --> 00:02:04,887
He’s saying, “How could you stay
away from Me for so long?”

28
00:02:04,887 --> 00:02:10,137
“In restless anticipation,
I await your return.”

29
00:02:10,137 --> 00:02:12,503
And He also gives an indication, 
He said,

30
00:02:12,503 --> 00:02:20,030
“But when this lifetime came and I had
some idea that this would be the lifetime,

31
00:02:20,030 --> 00:02:28,554
My anticipation—I couldn’t contain Myself,
waiting for you.”

32
00:02:28,554 --> 00:02:30,199
That’s Kṛṣṇa.

33
00:02:30,199 --> 00:02:38,609
That Kṛṣṇa, who can reciprocate every atom
of every heart’s hankering, simultaneously.

34
00:02:38,609 --> 00:02:41,583
“Prati aṅga lāge kā̐de prati aṅga mora.”

35
00:02:41,583 --> 00:02:45,053
“Akhila-rasāmṛta-mūrti Kṛṣṇa.”

36
00:02:45,053 --> 00:02:52,839
We have to remember, when we think that,
“Oh, He’s rasa personified”,

37
00:02:52,839 --> 00:02:56,061
and you might say, “Well, there are
many different types of rasas”,

38
00:02:56,061 --> 00:03:02,366
yes, so He has His many avatars,
incarnations, expansions,

39
00:03:02,366 --> 00:03:05,425
to accommodate everyone.

